# Phase 1 Closure Audit — Material Request + Forklift 2D Intake

> **Scope**: (A) Material Request flow, (B) Forklift 2D barcode scanning intake.
> **Audited against**: actual schema in `backend/src/db/schema/`, routes in `backend/src/routes/material-requests.ts`, specs `01`–`19`, and frontend types.

---

## 1) ✅ Phase-Closable Target Flow (E2E Narrative)

### Happy Path — end to end

```
 PRODUCTION                STORE                   FORKLIFT
 ──────────               ──────                  ──────────
 1. Create MR ──────────► 2. Approve MR
    (REQUESTED)              (APPROVED)
                           3. Allocate DOs
                              per line item
                           4. Confirm Issue ────► 5. See pending
                              (ISSUED)              handover batch
                                                  6. Pick material
                                                  7. Open Intake screen
                                                  8. Scan 2D barcode ×N
                                                  9. Finalize session
                                                     (INTAKE_COMPLETE)
                                                  ◄──── traceable ────►
```

**Step-by-step narrative:**

| # | Actor | Action | System effect |
|---|-------|--------|---------------|
| 1 | Production | Creates Material Request (MR) with model, BOM line items, requested quantities | MR = `REQUESTED`. Auto-generates `request_no` / `dmi_no`. |
| 2 | Store (approver) | Reviews and approves (or rejects) | MR → `APPROVED` (or `REJECTED`). Email notification. |
| 3 | Store | Allocates DO(s) per line item (issuer selects DO number, packs, qty) | `material_request_item_issues` rows created. `inventory_do.qty_issued` incremented. |
| 4 | Store | Confirms issue | MR → `ISSUED`. `handover_batch` auto-created with status `PENDING`. Forklift notified (SSE). |
| 5 | Forklift | Sees pending handover batches on dashboard | UI lists all `PENDING` handover batches. |
| 6 | Forklift | Physically picks material from store staging area | (Physical step — no system interaction.) |
| 7 | Forklift | Opens "Intake" screen, selects handover batch | `scan_session` created with status `OPEN`. |
| 8 | Forklift | Scans 2D barcode on each supplier pack | Per scan: parse → validate → match to issue line → create `scan_event` (immutable) → update `scanned_item` status. |
| 9 | Forklift | Finalizes intake | `scan_session` → `COMPLETED`. `handover_batch` → `RECEIVED`. If all batches for MR are received → MR → `INTAKE_COMPLETE`. |

### Phase-close criteria

- [x] Every material unit received has an immutable `scan_event` linking: **who** (forklift user), **when** (device + server timestamps), **what** (barcode raw data + parsed fields), **where** (device_id, station_id).
- [x] Full traceability chain: `material_request` → `item_issue` → `handover_batch` → `scan_session` → `scan_event` → `scanned_item` → `supplier_pack` → `inventory_do` → `supplier`.
- [x] Partial intake is tracked; finalizing with missing items is allowed with explicit acknowledgment.
- [x] No double-scan of the same barcode per MR.

---

## 2) 🔁 State Machines

### 2a) MaterialRequest (MR)

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> REQUESTED : Production creates
    REQUESTED --> APPROVED : Store approves
    REQUESTED --> REJECTED : Store rejects
    REQUESTED --> CANCELLED : Production cancels
    APPROVED --> ISSUED : Store confirms issue
    APPROVED --> CANCELLED : Store/Production cancels
    ISSUED --> INTAKE_COMPLETE : All handover batches RECEIVED
    ISSUED --> PARTIALLY_RECEIVED : ≥1 batch RECEIVED, not all
    PARTIALLY_RECEIVED --> INTAKE_COMPLETE : remaining batches received
    INTAKE_COMPLETE --> [*]
    REJECTED --> [*]
    CANCELLED --> [*]
```

| From | To | Who | Condition |
|------|----|-----|-----------|
| — | REQUESTED | production | Valid BOM lines, model active |
| REQUESTED | APPROVED | store (approver) | Approval authority per workflow_approval_configs |
| REQUESTED | REJECTED | store (approver) | Requires remarks |
| REQUESTED | CANCELLED | production / admin | Not yet approved |
| APPROVED | ISSUED | store (issuer) | ≥1 item_issue allocated, DO balances sufficient |
| APPROVED | CANCELLED | store / admin | Before issue only |
| ISSUED | PARTIALLY_RECEIVED | system (auto) | First handover batch marked RECEIVED |
| ISSUED | INTAKE_COMPLETE | system (auto) | All handover batches RECEIVED |
| PARTIALLY_RECEIVED | INTAKE_COMPLETE | system (auto) | All handover batches RECEIVED |

> **Audit gap found**: Current enum is `REQUESTED/APPROVED/REJECTED/ISSUED/CANCELLED`. Missing `PARTIALLY_RECEIVED` and `INTAKE_COMPLETE`. Migration required.

### 2b) HandoverBatch

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> PENDING : Auto-created on store issue confirm
    PENDING --> IN_TRANSIT : Forklift acknowledges pickup
    IN_TRANSIT --> RECEIVED : Forklift finalizes intake session (all scanned)
    IN_TRANSIT --> RECEIVED_PARTIAL : Forklift finalizes with missing items
    RECEIVED_PARTIAL --> RECEIVED : Missing items resolved (re-scan or exception close)
    PENDING --> CANCELLED : Store cancels before pickup
    RECEIVED --> [*]
    CANCELLED --> [*]
```

| From | To | Who | Condition |
|------|----|-----|-----------|
| — | PENDING | system | Auto on MR ISSUED |
| PENDING | IN_TRANSIT | forklift | Forklift acknowledges they have the material |
| IN_TRANSIT | RECEIVED | forklift | scan_session finalized, all expected items matched |
| IN_TRANSIT | RECEIVED_PARTIAL | forklift | Finalized with acknowledged shortages |
| RECEIVED_PARTIAL | RECEIVED | forklift / admin | Missing items resolved |
| PENDING | CANCELLED | store / admin | Before forklift pickup |

### 2c) ScanSession

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> OPEN : Forklift starts scanning
    OPEN --> COMPLETED : Forklift finalizes
    OPEN --> ABANDONED : Timeout / explicit abandon
    COMPLETED --> [*]
    ABANDONED --> [*]
```

| From | To | Who |
|------|----|-----|
| — | OPEN | forklift |
| OPEN | COMPLETED | forklift (finalize action) |
| OPEN | ABANDONED | forklift / system (30-min inactivity timeout) |

### 2d) ScanEvent (immutable — no transitions)

Every `scan_event` is written once and never modified. The `result` field records the outcome:

| Result | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| `MATCHED` | Barcode parsed and matched to an issue line successfully |
| `DUPLICATE` | Same barcode already scanned for this MR |
| `NOT_FOUND` | Barcode part_number/DO not in issued list |
| `EXPIRED` | Barcode parsed but material is past expiry policy |
| `PARSE_ERROR` | Barcode could not be parsed |
| `MISMATCH` | Part number doesn't match any expected line |

