#### 5.7 Scan Event — Submit single scan

> **This is the hot path.** Must be fast (<100ms p95).

```
POST /scan-sessions/:sessionId/scans
Auth: JWT (role: forklift)
```

```json
// Request
{
  "idempotency_key": "client-uuid-v4",
  "barcode_raw": "RS P PIN430-A-001 RS Q 100 RS V SUP001 RS T LOT2026-A RS D 20260215",
  "scanned_at_device": "2026-03-02T10:20:05.123Z",
  "device_id": "uuid"
}

// Response 200 — successful match
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "scan_event_id": "uuid",
    "result": "MATCHED",
    "result_detail": null,
    "matched_item": {
      "part_number": "PIN430-A-001",
      "do_number": "DO-2026-001",
      "scanned_packs": 3,
      "expected_packs": 5,
      "remaining": 2
    },
    "session_totals": {
      "total_scans": 10,
      "matched": 9,
      "errors": 1
    }
  }
}

// Response 200 — scan error (DUPLICATE / NOT_FOUND / etc.)
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "scan_event_id": "uuid",
    "result": "DUPLICATE",
    "result_detail": "Already scanned: PIN430-A-001 LOT2026-A pack 3",
    "matched_item": null,
    "session_totals": { "total_scans": 11, "matched": 9, "errors": 2 }
  }
}
```

**Idempotency**: If `idempotency_key` already exists, return the existing result without side effects.

**Concurrency**: Use `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE` on `handover_batch_items` row when incrementing `scanned_packs`.

---

#### 5.8 Scan Session — Finalize

```
POST /scan-sessions/:sessionId/finalize
Auth: JWT (role: forklift)
```

```json
// Request
{
  "acknowledge_shortages": true,
  "shortage_remarks": "2 packs PIN430 not received, will follow up",
  "acknowledge_overages": false
}

// Response 200
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "session_id": "uuid",
    "status": "COMPLETED",
    "handover_batch_status": "RECEIVED",
    "material_request_status": "INTAKE_COMPLETE",
    "summary": {
      "expected_packs": 15,
      "scanned_packs": 13,
      "shortages": [
        { "part_number": "PIN430-A-001", "expected": 5, "scanned": 3, "missing": 2 }
      ],
      "overages": []
    }
  }
}
```

**Business rules on finalize**:
- If all items fully scanned → `handover_batch` → `RECEIVED`
- If shortages exist and `acknowledge_shortages = true` → `handover_batch` → `RECEIVED_PARTIAL`
- If shortages exist and `acknowledge_shortages = false` → reject finalize
- After batch status update, check all batches for MR: if all `RECEIVED` or `RECEIVED_PARTIAL` → MR → `INTAKE_COMPLETE`

---

#### 5.9 Exception — Return to Store

```
POST /handover-batches/:id/return-to-store
Auth: JWT (role: forklift, admin)
```

```json
// Request
{
  "reason": "Wrong material received",
  "items": [
    { "batch_item_id": "uuid", "return_packs": 2, "remark": "Wrong lot" }
  ]
}

// Response 200
{
  "success": true,
  "data": { "id": "uuid", "status": "PENDING", "return_logged": true }
}
```

---

#### 5.10 Error Codes (new, additive to existing catalog)

| Code | HTTP | Meaning |
|------|------|---------|
| `HANDOVER_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Batch ID invalid |
| `HANDOVER_WRONG_STATUS` | 409 | Batch not in expected status for this action |
| `SESSION_ALREADY_OPEN` | 409 | Another OPEN session exists for this batch |
| `SESSION_NOT_OPEN` | 409 | Trying to submit scan to non-OPEN session |
| `BARCODE_PARSE_FAILED` | 422 | Cannot extract fields from barcode |
| `BARCODE_DUPLICATE` | 409 | Same barcode already MATCHED in this batch |
| `BARCODE_NOT_IN_ISSUE` | 422 | Part number not in issued items |
| `BARCODE_EXPIRED` | 422 | Material past expiry |
| `SHORTAGE_NOT_ACKNOWLEDGED`| 422 | Finalize refused — shortages not acknowledged |
| `IDEMPOTENCY_CONFLICT` | 409 | Idempotency key reused with different payload |

